      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Lee Lodge, ¶ Strangeways Terrace, W.A ¶ . ¶ North Adelaide?Chalmers, originally booked on RMSOrientto Sydney, left the vessel when it arrived in Adelaide on 3 August, and intended to remain a few days...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.08.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Chalmers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A38 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia, (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Rec &amp; answ 7/8/87.' Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">Lee Lodge,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">Strangeways Terrace, W.A</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>North Adelaide?<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Chalmers, originally booked on RMS<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Orient<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>to Sydney, left the vessel when it arrived in Adelaide on 3 August, and intended to remain a few days before travelling by train to Melbourne, where he planned to '<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">meet the leading members of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia … and come to a settlement with them with respect to explorations he may make under the auspices of the Society'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>((<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'The Rev James Chalmers in Adelaide',</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">South Australian register</seg>, 4 August, p. 5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4 Aug: 1887</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for your kind telegram just received.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Telegram not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would have wired you yesterday on my arrival but I was uncertain as to my movements — Friends here are particularly anxious I should remain until after next Wednesday night<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>10 August. While in Adelaide he lectured at a meeting of the SA Branch of the Society on 9 August (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'Lecture on New Guinea'</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">South Australian register</seg>, 10 August, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; I having arranged for our "Ellengowan" to meet me at Cooktown<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on the 10 Sep. I shall have time — It would afford me much pleasure &amp; satisfaction to be present at your Council meeting on Tuesday evening but, on that day I have arranged to meet a number of ministers.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Chalmers arrived in Melbourne by train on 13 August (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'NEW GUINEA AND ITS PROSPECTS. the rev. james chalmer's views</seg>.',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 15 August, 1887, p. 7) and met the Council of the Society at its meeting on 15 August (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'royal geographical society'</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>20 August, 1867, p. 15).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Despite his reported intention to enter into an arrangement with the Council (n. 2 above), at a lecture by Chalmers at the Collins Street Independent Church on 23 August, M is reported to have '<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">expressed the regret of the Geographical Society, that Mr Chalmers could not lead their exploring expedition, but Mr. Chalmers is before all things a missionary, treading in the steps of Livingstone' (</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">c</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">halmers on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">n</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">ew<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">g</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">uinea'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Herald</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne), 24 August 1887. p. 4).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall be able to spend some time in Melbourne &amp; so shall have opportunity of conferring with you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enjoyed my visit home very much indeed &amp; have returned much benefitted.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me my dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours most truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Chalmers</p>
         </div>
      </body>
